val Riza Kayaalp of Turkey beat him in the final of the 2015 World Championships.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u0131za_Kayaalp\", \"score\": 0.9999999825752185, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Riza Kayaalp\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u0131za_Kayaalp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/R\\u0131za_Kayaalp\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9777295807148171, \"rank\": 0.02277542658417667, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lopez's 6-0 victory over silver medalist Yasmani Acosta of Chile at the Champ de Mars arena is still remarkable because the Cuban had not competed since winning his fourth gold in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 661, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yasmani Acosta\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yasmani_Acosta\"}, {\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8532789153398425, \"rank\": 0.17063609325213158, \"text\": \"Chile\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 744, \"end\": 749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9985232407291226, \"rank\": 0.0014789234685624482, \"text\": \"Cuban\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3897465010068283e-18, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lopez pinned his former training partner Acosta in the first period and then added a takedown in the second to secure victory before removing his shoes and leaving them on the mat signaling his retirement.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a moment to demonstrate that someone has retired officially from the sport of wrestling and that also leaves a path wide open for the younger generation to continue inspiring others,\\\" said Lopez.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To achieve all of these results, one has to love their sport, love their job, and demonstrate to the world that with so little you can achieve great things,\\\" he said of his career.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His celebration also included a takedown of one of his coaches and lifting the other.\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lopez touched the mat with his head, gleaming with beads of sweat, before taking off his shoes.\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cuba-born Acosta was left with mixed emotions.\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted to win gold but at the same time, not so much because it's Mijain, a legend in wrestling worldwide,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have known each other for a long time now.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We did the trials together for this year's Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has been giving me advice in every phase, so he's everything, a rival, a friend, he's a brother.\\\"\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also in the Greco-Roman section, in which holds below the waist are prohibited, Japan's Kenichiro Fumita won the 60kg gold with a 4-1 win against Cao Liguo of China, who took silver.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2057, \"end\": 2062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999974671877924, \"rank\": 2.133886878456259e-06, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenichiro_Fumita\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kenichiro Fumita\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenichiro_Fumita\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenichiro_Fumita\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's 68kg final, Amit Elor of the Unites States won the gold, while Meerim Zhumanazarova of Kyrgyzstan won silver.\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2239, \"end\": 2259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meerim_Zhumanazarova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Meerim Zhumanazarova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meerim_Zhumanazarova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meerim_Zhumanazarova\"}, {\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyrgyzstan\", \"score\": 0.9999999985379873, \"rank\": 1.4603268984341369e-09, \"text\": \"Kyrgyzstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyrgyzstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyrgyzstan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Buse Tosun Cavusoglu of Turkey and N